Week 1 Practical Journal on Skillink Application

Learning Activities & Resources

- Explored the fundamentals of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript through online tutorials and documentation.
- Reviewed the GitHub repository of the SkillLink job board application to understand its structure and implementation. 

- Watched a YouTube tutorial on building mobile applications using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. 

Estimated Hours

Approximately 8 hours

Content Insights

This week, I focused on understanding how HTML, CSS, and JavaScript can be utilized to develop dynamic web applications. HTML provides the structural foundation of web pages, CSS is used for styling and layout, and JavaScript adds interactivity and functionality. By combining these technologies, developers can create responsive and engaging user experiences. The SkillLink application, for instance, leverages these technologies to allow job seekers to search and filter job postings based on their preferences and interests. 

Career/Employability/Learning Insights

Proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript is essential for a career in web development. These technologies form the backbone of modern web applications and are highly valued in the job market. Understanding how to effectively use them enables the creation of user-friendly and accessible web applications, which is crucial for enhancing user engagement and satisfaction. This knowledge aligns with my career goals in cybersecurity, as building secure web applications requires a solid understanding of these foundational technologies. 
